    "title": "Adjectives (continued): States and Time",
    "explanation": "Le chapeau tombe ici. Darwin dort ici. — these are not actions done TO something, but states: falling, sleeping.\n\nNotice time words: longtemps (a long time), tard (late), juste (just). They tell WHEN.\n\nRe-read and separate action verbs (chercher, trouver) from state verbs (dormir, tomber). How are they different?"
